{{BLP sources|date=November 2011}} {{Infobox writer |birth_name = Per Håkan Stefan Nilsson |period = [[19th-century philosophy]] |image = Per_Nilsson 02.JPG |image_size = 250px |caption = Per Nilsson in 2013 |birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1954|02|13}} |birth_place = [[Möllevången]], [[Malmö]], [[Sweden]] |death_date = |death_place = |years_active = 1986-present |residence = [[Sölvesborg]], [[Sweden]] |nationality = [[Swedes|Swedish]] |occupation = Writer, musician |signature =Per Nilsson's Signature.svg }} '''Per Nilsson''' is a Swedish author.He worked as a [[music teacher]] until the summer of 1999, after which he became a full-time [[author]]. He has also written the [[screenplay]] ''Hannah with H'', based on his early novel ''Another way to be young''. Between 1997 and 2010, he was a Member the Swedish Children's Book College.
