{{distinguish|Yanam language}} {{Infobox language |name=Shiriana |nativename=Bahwana |states=[[Brazil]] |extinct=? |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2=Northern |fam3=[[Upper Amazon Arawakan|Upper Amazonian]] |fam4=Manao? |iso3=xir |glotto=xiri1243 |glottorefname=Xiriâna }}
'''Shiriana''' (Xiriâna, Chiriana), or '''Bahuana''' (Bahwana), is an unclassified Upper Amazon [[Arawakan]] language once spoken by the [[Shiriana people]] of [[Roraima]], [[Brazil]]. It had an [[active–stative]] syntax.<ref>Aikhenvald, "Arawak", in Dixon & Aikhenvald, eds., ''The Amazonian Languages'', 1999.</ref>
